{"key":"processedPost-16387633","value":{"id":16387633,"first":16387539,"last":17418701,"when":1339818288,"utime":"06/16/12 06:44 AM","content":"Stamets says four to five air exchanges hourly, but that's just to give a rough idea.&nbsp; Four to five air exchanges per hour with one 1/2 pint substrate is a lot different than four to five air exchanges with 20.<br /><br />There's nothing stealthy about an air pump buzzing under a dresser.&nbsp; That attracts far more attention than a shotgun terrarium in the middle of the room.&nbsp; Have some oyster mushrooms mixed in, since they're faster than cubes to colonize and fruit, and they grow fine on <a href=\"http://www.mushroomvideos.com/BRF-Pf-Tek\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\">brf cakes</a>.&nbsp; The best place to hide a grow is right out in the open.&nbsp; If someone asks, pick off a couple of oysters and fry them up in some butter.<br />RR<br /><a href=\"https://files.shroomery.org/files/07-007/139225721-pf_oysters_010a.jpg\" class=\"highslide\" onclick=\"return hs.expand(this,{slideshowGroup:'hsg1'})\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"max-width:192px;height:auto;\" src=\"/forums/thumbs/07-007/139225721-thumb_pf_oysters_010a.jpg\"></a> <a href=\"https://files.shroomery.org/files/07-007/139225730-pf_oysters_011a.jpg\" class=\"highslide\" onclick=\"return hs.expand(this,{slideshowGroup:'hsg1'})\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"max-width:192px;height:auto;\" src=\"/forums/thumbs/07-007/139225730-thumb_pf_oysters_011a.jpg\"></a>","title":"Re: PMP-how do i determine the size airpump i need?","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}